        "InitialTop": -1022.4065360890904,
        "InitialHeight": 688.69781838953736,
        "TextblockHeight": 129.6,
        "Background": "#FFFF7BAC"
      },
      {
        "Id": "51630e57e0d04373a511c91a8aba1819",
        "Title": "Excel Data Extractor-reads the utility matrix and organizes it to hand off",
        "DescriptionText": "Description:\nOpens the Utility Matrix Excel file and reads the Main sheet, pulling only the columns defined in the mapping list. Filters rows down to recognized Connection ID prefixes (CA, DRN, EL, EX, HH, INT, PCW, PHW, TD) and automatically excludes anything marked Obsolete. The extracted data is packaged into a structured dictionary with flat and grouped outputs for clean consumption by downstream nodes. If the file is open in Excel when the script runs, it prompts the user to close it before retrying rather than failing silently.",
        "IsExpanded": true,
        "WidthAdjustment": 0.0,
        "HeightAdjustment": 0.0,
        "Nodes": [
          "7359c054c20c40e8ab450ecb03ab2925",
          "4db0cfea468a4f1cab4dd4de2ff58c94"
        ],
        "HasNestedGroups": false,
        "Left": -1223.9615283535727,
        "Top": 78.280470739071191,
        "Width": 1190.031971698945,
        "Height": 931.93766000722781,
        "FontSize": 36.0,
        "InitialTop": 189.08047073907119,
        "InitialHeight": 851.13766000722785,
        "TextblockHeight": 100.8,
        "Background": "#FF48B9FF"
      },
      {
        "Id": "de5d45a5b08143b3ac4c2444bf0a35e8",
        "Title": "Updates the parameters according to util matrix\r\n",
        "DescriptionText": "Description:\nRuns after ConMan has finished placing and moving connectors. Reads the UM-Revit Mapping sheet directly from the Utility Matrix Excel file to determine which parameters apply to which connector family, then compares every mapped field against what's currently in Revit and writes only what has changed. Matches connectors from the specified categories to Excel rows using Connection ID as the key. Includes a fallback for connector families not listed in the mapping sheet — if the parameter physically exists on the element it gets written regardless. Outputs a full before/after report for every connector processed, ready for the Excel report generator.",
        "IsExpanded": true,
        "WidthAdjustment": 0.0,
        "HeightAdjustment": 0.0,
        "Nodes": [
          "c63b908678d3433483bf5f432e01e56a",
          "2c483f59f1ee4faaab4ceba273490d46",
          "3ddc11c17797421da56fefe03acb8984"
        ],
        "HasNestedGroups": false,
        "Left": 400.5437527754957,
        "Top": 104.16212441888692,
        "Width": 1081.6145509251196,
        "Height": 748.04580000673241,
        "FontSize": 36.0,
        "InitialTop": 272.56212441888692,
        "InitialHeight": 609.64580000673232,
        "TextblockHeight": 158.4,
        "Background": "#FF71C6A8"
      },
      {
        "Id": "4221c0283de9471e99c1db4f779917d8",
        "Title": "Excel Report Generator",
        "DescriptionText": "Description:\nTakes the output data from upstream nodes and writes it into a formatted, multi-sheet Excel workbook. Automatically detects the data type for each sheet — if headers contain Original/Updated column pairs it formats the sheet as a Comparison report with row-level change highlighting and a summary block, otherwise it formats it as a clean Simple table with alternating row striping. Saves to the specified path and falls back to the Desktop if the path is invalid, or saves a timestamped copy if the file is already open. Always opens the file automatically on completion. Includes a Script Log sheet on every run showing timestamped execution details, warnings, and errors.",
        "IsExpanded": true,
        "WidthAdjustment": 0.0,
        "HeightAdjustment": 0.0,
